    <!-- Why 1-on-1 -->
    <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold mt-10 mb-4">Why 1-on-1 Tutoring Makes a Difference</h2>
    <p class="text-gray-600 mb-4 leading-relaxed">Group classes and apps can help you practice, but they cannot adapt to your specific needs. In a group class, the teacher moves at the pace of the average student. In a 1-on-1 session, every minute is focused on you.</p>
    <p class="text-gray-600 mb-4 leading-relaxed">A good 1-on-1 tutor identifies your weak points, corrects your mistakes in real time, and builds a lesson plan around your goals. Whether you are preparing for a job interview, an exam, or just want to speak more confidently, personal attention accelerates your progress in ways group learning rarely can.</p>
    <p class="text-gray-600 mb-6 leading-relaxed">The good news is that 1-on-1 tutoring is no longer only for people with large budgets. Several platforms now offer quality personal lessons for under $15 per session.</p>

    <!-- See Guru -->
    <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold mt-10 mb-4">See Guru: Best Value 1-on-1 Tutoring</h2>
    <div class="bg-green-50 border border-green-300 rounded-xl p-4 mb-6">
      <p class="font-bold text-green-800">Our #1 Recommendation for Under $15</p>
      <p class="text-sm text-green-700">Real 1-on-1 lessons from $3 with no subscription required. Great for learners who want personal attention at the lowest possible price.</p>
    </div>
    <p class="text-gray-600 mb-4 leading-relaxed"><a href="/reviews/see-guru/" class="text-green-700 font-semibold underline">See Guru</a> is the most affordable true 1-on-1 option we found. Lessons start at just $3 per session, and you book directly with the tutor you choose. There is no subscription, no package requirement, and no pressure to buy more than you need.</p>
    <p class="text-gray-600 mb-4 leading-relaxed">Each lesson is a private session between you and your tutor. You set the goals, choose the topics, and control the pace. This makes See Guru especially useful for learners who have specific needs, like preparing for a presentation at work, practicing for a visa interview, or working on pronunciation.</p>
    <p class="text-gray-600 mb-4 leading-relaxed">The trade-off is a smaller tutor pool compared to larger platforms. Filtering for specific specializations like legal English or medical English may return fewer results. However, for general conversational practice, exam prep, or business English at an affordable price, See Guru delivers strong value.</p>

    <!-- iTalki -->
    <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold mt-10 mb-4">iTalki: Most Tutor Options Under $15</h2>
    <p class="text-gray-600 mb-4 leading-relaxed"><a href="/reviews/italki/" class="text-blue-700 font-semibold underline">iTalki</a> has the largest selection of tutors under $15. Community tutors, who are fluent speakers without formal teaching certifications, typically charge between $4 and $10 per lesson. Many offer excellent conversational practice at this price range.</p>
    <p class="text-gray-600 mb-4 leading-relaxed">iTalki also has professional tutors with formal qualifications starting around $10 to $15 per lesson. If you want certified teachers at the $15 ceiling, you will find them here. The platform allows detailed filtering by price, language, specialty, and availability, making it easy to find a good match within your budget.</p>
    <p class="text-gray-600 mb-4 leading-relaxed">All iTalki lessons are 1-on-1 video sessions. You can book trial lessons with most tutors to check the fit before committing to regular sessions.</p>

    <!-- Preply -->
    <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold mt-10 mb-4">Preply: Best for Structured 1-on-1 Learning</h2>
    <p class="text-gray-600 mb-4 leading-relaxed"><a href="/reviews/preply/" class="text-purple-700 font-semibold underline">Preply</a> starts at around $10 per lesson for most tutors, putting it at the upper end of the $15 budget. What you get for the slightly higher price includes a structured curriculum, lesson recording, a built-in vocabulary trainer, and conversation topics organized by level.</p>
    <p class="text-gray-600 mb-4 leading-relaxed">Preply has over 50,000 tutors, so you have more choice than almost any other platform. Free trial lessons let you test a tutor before buying a package. For learners who want a clear study path and access to experienced tutors, Preply at $10 to $15 per lesson is worth the investment.</p>

    <!-- Cambly -->
    <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold mt-10 mb-4">Cambly: 1-on-1 Conversations on a Budget</h2>
    <p class="text-gray-600 mb-4 leading-relaxed"><a href="/reviews/cambly/" class="text-orange-700 font-semibold underline">Cambly</a> operates on a subscription model. Unlimited conversations start at $99 per month, which works out to roughly $3 to $4 per session if you use it regularly. All tutors on Cambly are native English speakers.</p>
    <p class="text-gray-600 mb-4 leading-relaxed">If you plan to take three or more lessons per week, Cambly can be excellent value. The 1-on-1 sessions are real conversations, and you can book tutors who specialize in areas like business English or exam prep. However, Cambly is less structured than platforms with formal curricula. If you want a clear lesson plan, Preply or iTalki professional tutors are better suited.</p>

    <!-- Verbling -->
    <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold mt-10 mb-4">Verbling: Best for Targeted Language Coaching</h2>
    <p class="text-gray-600 mb-4 leading-relaxed"><a href="/reviews/verbling/" class="text-teal-700 font-semibold underline">Verbling</a> starts at $15 per lesson, sitting right at the edge of this comparison range. The platform has a strong reputation for connecting learners with experienced language coaches who offer personalized, conversation-driven sessions.</p>
    <p class="text-gray-600 mb-4 leading-relaxed">Verbling is best for learners who want to focus on specific areas like accent reduction, business vocabulary, or cultural fluency. Tutors on the platform tend to be more experienced, and the pay-per-lesson model means you only pay for what you book.</p>

    <!-- Verdict -->
    <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold mt-10 mb-4">Our Verdict</h2>
    <p class="text-gray-600 mb-4 leading-relaxed">For the best value 1-on-1 tutoring under $15, <strong>See Guru</strong> is our top pick. Starting at $3 per lesson with no subscription, it offers real personal attention at the lowest price we found. It is ideal for budget learners who need flexibility.</p>
    <p class="text-gray-600 mb-4 leading-relaxed">If you want more tutor options and filtering tools, <strong>iTalki</strong> community tutors from $4 to $10 per lesson offer excellent variety. For structured lessons with a clear curriculum, <strong>Preply</strong> at $10 per lesson delivers strong value despite sitting at the higher end of the budget range.</p>
    <p class="text-gray-600 mb-6 leading-relaxed">For frequent learners who will use three or more sessions per week, <strong>Cambly</strong> subscriptions work out to under $4 per conversation and give you unlimited access to native English tutors.</p>

    <!-- See Guru CTA -->
    <div class="bg-green-50 border border-green-200 rounded-xl p-6 mt-8">
      <p class="font-bold text-lg mb-2">Try See Guru for 1-on-1 Lessons</p>
      <p class="text-sm text-gray-600 mb-4">Book personal lessons from $3 with no subscription. Find a tutor who fits your goals and budget today.</p>
      <a href="/reviews/see-guru/" class="inline-block bg-green-600 text-white font-bold px-6 py-3 rounded-lg hover:bg-green-700">Try See Guru</a>
    </div>

    <!-- FAQ -->
    <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold mt-10 mb-4">Frequently Asked Questions</h2>
    <div class="space-y-4 mb-8">
      <div class="border border-gray-200 rounded-xl p-4">
        <h3 class="font-bold text-gray-800 mb-2">Are tutors under $15 per lesson actually good?</h3>
        <p class="text-gray-600">Yes. Many excellent tutors charge moderate rates. Community tutors on iTalki, for example, charge $4 to $10 per lesson and often provide high-quality conversational practice. Price alone is not a reliable quality indicator. Look at tutor reviews, response rates, and intro videos before booking.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="border border-gray-200 rounded-xl p-4">
        <h3 class="font-bold text-gray-800 mb-2">Can I get a native English speaker for under $15?</h3>
        <p class="text-gray-600">Sometimes. Platforms like iTalki and Preply have native English speakers at various price points. On iTalki, you may find community tutors who are native speakers at $8 to $12 per lesson. On Cambly, native-only tutors are available through subscription. See Guru has a limited selection of native speakers.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="border border-gray-200 rounded-xl p-4">
        <h3 class="font-bold text-gray-800 mb-2">Do I need to subscribe or buy a package?</h3>
        <p class="text-gray-600">Not on See Guru, iTalki, or Verbling. Those platforms let you book and pay for individual lessons. Cambly and Lingoda require subscriptions. If you prefer pay-per-lesson flexibility, stick with the former three.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="border border-gray-200 rounded-xl p-4">
        <h3 class="font-bold text-gray-800 mb-2">How do I find the best tutor for my goals under $15?</h3>
        <p class="text-gray-600">Use filters. On iTalki, set your price range, select your target language, and filter by specialty (business, exam prep, conversation). Read at least three reviews per tutor before booking. Book a trial lesson first whenever possible.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="border border-gray-200 rounded-xl p-4">
        <h3 class="font-bold text-gray-800 mb-2">What is the best platform for exam prep under $15?</h3>
        <p class="text-gray-600">iTalki is our top pick for exam prep under $15. Look for community tutors with positive reviews mentioning IELTS, TOEFL, or your target exam. Many have specific experience with these tests. See Guru also has tutors who specialize in exam preparation.</p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </article>
  <Footer />
</Base>
